law.text:
As used in KRS 209.550 to 209.554, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Commissioner" means the commissioner of the department;
"Department" means the Department for Public Health;
"Documentation" means written evidence from an individual's health care provider that indicates the date and place the individual received the influenza vaccine or the pneumococcal vaccine;
"Employee" means an individual who is employed, directly or by contract, with another entity, on a part-time or full-time basis;
"Medically contraindicated" describes a situation in which the influenza or pneumococcal vaccine should not be administered to an individual because of a condition that the individual has that will be detrimental to the individual's health if the individual receives the vaccine; and
"Long-term care facility" has the same meaning as in KRS 216.510, except that for purposes of KRS 209.550 to 209.554, "long-term care facility" does not include family-care homes or personal-care homes.
